'' || Anoushka Shankar || EMI Angel\n|-\n| 2001 || ''Vairagya'' || Ajoy Chakraborty || Navras Records\n|-\n| 2001 || ''Live at Carnegie Hall'' || Anoushka Shankar || EMI Angel\n|-\n| 2001 || ''Full Circle: Carnegie Hall'' (Grammy winning title)<ref name=list>{{cite news |last=Suhasini |first=Lalitha |date=4 October 2005 |title=Percussionist Bikram Ghosh revisits his roots in the folk fusion album called Folktail |url=http://cities.expressindia.com/fullstory.php?newsid=151414 |newspaper=Mumbai Newsline |publisher=The Indian Express |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060222093323/http://cities.expressindia.com/fullstory.php?newsid=151414 |archivedate=22 February 2006 |accessdate=3 April 2009}}</ref> || Ravi Shankar || EMI Angel\n|-\n| 2001 || ''Hypnotic Santoor'' || Tarun Bhattacharya || Biswas\n|-\n| 2002 || ''In Portrait'' || Ravi Shankar || Naxos\n|-\n| 2002 || ''Raga Basant Mukhari'' || Tarun Bhattacharya || India Archives\n|-\n| 2004 || ''Raga Rasa: That Which Colors The Mind'' || [[Kartik Seshadri]] || [[Harold Hagopian|Traditional Crossroads]]\n|-\n| 2005 || ''A Spiritual Journey'' || Tarun Bhattacharya || Universal Music \n|-\n| 2005 || ''Rise'' || Anoushka Shankar || [[Angel Records]]\n|-\n| 2006 || ''Raag Rageshri'' || Tarun Bhattacharya || [[Universal Music Group|Universal Music]]\n|-\n| 2008 || ''Musical Horizon'' || Tarun Bhattacharya || Horizon\n|-\n| 2010 || ''Crossroads'' || [[Tejendra Majumdar|Tejendra Narayan Majumdar]] || Indya\n|-\n| 2011 || ''The Very Best of Ravi Shankar'' || Ravi Shankar || EMI Classics\n|}\n\n'''Experimental accompaniment'''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Album !! Main Artist !! Record Label\n|-\n| 1992 || ''Songs of Nature'' || [[Vishwa Mohan Bhatt]], Tarun Bhattacharya, Ronu Majumdar || Original Music Impressions\n|-\n| 1993 || ''Travellers Tale'' || [[Ronu Majumdar]] || Magnasound/ OMI\n|-\n| 2005 || ''Spirits'' || U. Rajesh, [[Pete Lockett]] || Living Media India/ Music Today\n|-\n| 2006 || ''Golden Krithis