.footystamps.com/st_team_of_the_century.htm |publisher=footystamps.com.au |accessdate=3 November 2009}}</ref>\n| backpocket1 = [[Barry Lawrence]]\n| fullback = [[Verdun Howell]]\n| backpocket2 = [[Kevin Neale]]\n| halfbackflank1 = [[Trevor Barker]]\n| centrehalfback = [[Neil Roberts (Australian footballer)|Neil Roberts]]\n| halfbackflank2 = [[Daryl Griffiths (Australian rules footballer)|Daryl Griffiths]]\n| wing1 = [[Nicky Winmar]]\n| centre = [[Ian Stewart (Australian rules footballer)|Ian Stewart]]\n| wing2 = [[Lance Oswald]]\n| halfforwardflank1 = [[Stewart Loewe]]\n| centrehalfforward = [[Darrel Baldock]] (C)\n| halfforwardflank2 = [[Bill Mohr]]\n| forwardpocket1 = [[Dave McNamara]]\n| fullforward = [[Tony Lockett]]\n| forwardpocket2 = [[Nathan Burke]]\n| ruck = [[Carl Ditterich]]\n| ruckrover = [[Robert Harvey (footballer)|Robert Harvey]]\n| rover = [[Ross G. Smith|Ross Smith]]\n| interchange1 = [[Barry Breen]]\n| interchange2 = [[Bob Murray (Australian footballer)|Bob Murray]]\n| interchange3 = [[Alan Morrow]]\n| interchange4 = [[Jim A. Ross|Jim Ross]]\n| interchange5 =\n| interchange6 =\n| coach = [[Allan Jeans]]\n}}\n\n==Women's teams==\nIn 2017, following the inaugural [[AFL Women's]] (AFLW) season, St Kilda was among eight clubs that applied for licences to enter the competition from 2019 onwards.<ref>{{cite news |last=Schmook |first=Nathan |title=Decision on AFLW expansion delayed |url=http://www.afl.com.au/news/2017-08-29/decision-over-aflw-expansion-delayed |work=afl.com.au |date=29 August 2017 |accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref> In September 2017, the club was announced as one of four clubs to receive a licence to join the competition in 2020.<ref>{{cite news |last=Black |first=Sarah |title=North and Geelong win AFLW expansion race |url=http://www.afl.com.au/news/2017-09-27/afl-set-to-reveal-new-womens-teams-for-2019 |work=afl.com.au |date=27 September 2017 |accessdate=5 April 2018}}</ref> The club has also fielded a team in the second-tier [[VFL Women's]] league since 2018, in partnership with VFL men's club [[Frankston Football Club|Frankston]]. The team is referred to as the ''Southern Saints''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vfl.com.au/clubs/vfl-womens-clubs/southern-saints/|title=Southern Saints|work=VFL.com.au}}</ref>\n\n{{St Kilda AFL Women's current squad}}\n\n=== Season summaries ===\n'''AFL Women's'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;font-size: 87%\"\n! colspan=\"9\" | St Kilda AFLW honour roll\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;font-size: 87%;\"\n! Season !! Final position\n!Coach\n!Captain(s)!! Best and fairest !! Leading goal kicker\n|-style=\"font-size: 87%;\"\n|-style=\"font-size: 87%;\"\n|[[2020 AFL Women's season|2020]]\n|8th ^\n|[[Peta Searle]]\n|[[Cat Phillips]], [[Kate Shierlaw]] & [[Rhiannon Watt]]\n|TBC\n|[[Caitlin Greiser]] (10) [[AFL Women's leading goalkicker|\u272a]]\n|}\n<small>^ Denotes the ladder was split into two or more conferences. These numbers refer to the club's overall finishing position that season.</small>\n\n'''VFL Women's'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;font-size: 87%\"\n! colspan=\"9\" | Southern Saints VFLW honour roll\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;font-size: 87%;\"\n! Season !! Final position\n!Coach\n!Captain!! Best and fairest !! Leading goal kicker\n|-style=\"font-size: 87%;\"\n|2018\n|8th\n|[[Peta Searle]]\n|[[Georgia Walker]]\n|[[Alison Drennan]] & [[Rhiannon Watt]]\n|[[Tara Bohanna]] (15)\n|-\n|-style=\"font-size: 87%;\"\n|2019\n|3rd\n|[[Peta Searle]]\n|''Rotating captains''\n|[[Tilly Lucas-Rodd]]\n|[[Caitlin Greiser]] (22)\n|}\n<small>Sources: [https://vfl.com.au/southern-saints-historical-data/ Club historical data] and [http://websites.sportstg.com/comp_info.cgi?c=1-118-0-518546-0&pool=1001&round=0&a=STATS VFLW stats]</small>\n\n==Coaches==\n{{Main|List of St Kilda Football Club coaches}}\n\n==Club officials==\n{{col-float |firstcol=24em}}\n\n===Corporate management===\n* President: [[Andrew Bassat]]\n* Vice-president: [[Russell Caplan]]\n* Chief executive officer: [[Matt Finnis]]\n* Director: [[Dean Anderson]]\n* Director: [[Jennifer Douglas]]\n* Director: Paul Kirk <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.saints.com.au/news/227904/paul-kirk |title=Paul Kirk |website=St Kilda Football Club |accessdate=14 January 2020}}</ref>\n* Director: [[Jack Rush]]\n* Director: [[Danielle Roche|Danni Roche]]\n* Director: [[Adam Hilton]]\n{{col-float-break |nextcol=36em}}\n\n===Team management===\n* Senior Coach: [[Brett Ratten]]\n* Assistant: [[Brendon Lade]]\n* Assistant: [[Aaron Hamill]]\n* Assistant: [[Adam Skrobalak]]\n* Assistant: [[Robbie Chancellor]]\n* VFL Coach and Development Manager: [[Ben McGlynn]]\n* Development Coach: Jake Batchelor\n* Head of Football Program: [[David Rath]]\n* Leadership and Development Program: [[Billy Slater]]\n* Football Operations Assistant: [[Jarryd Roughead]]\n{{col-float-end}}\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n* '''[[Australian Football League|VFL/AFL grand finals]]'''\n** '''Premiers (1)''': [[1966 VFL Grand Final|1966]]\n** ''Runners up (6)'': [[1913 VFL Grand Final|1913]], [[1965 VFL Grand Final|1965]], [[1971 VFL Grand Final|1971]], [[1997 AFL Grand Final|1997]], [[2009 AFL Grand Final|2009]], [[2010 AFL Grand Final|2010]]\n*'''[[VFL/AFL pre-season competition]]'''\n** '''Premiers (3)''': [[1996 Ansett Australia Cup|1996]], [[2004 Wizard Home Loans Cup|2004]], [[2008 NAB Cup|2008]]\n** ''Runners up (2)'': [[1998 Ansett Australia Cup|1998]], [[2010 NAB Cup|2010]]\n*'''[[VFL Night Series]]'''\n** '''Premiers (1)''': [[1958 Night Series Cup|1958]],\n** ''Runners up (1)'': [[1964 Night Series Cup|1964]]\n*'''VFL/AFL Lightning Premiership'''\n** '''Premiers (1)''': [[1940 VFL Lightning Premiership|1940]]\n** ''Runners up (1)'': [[1953 VFL Lightning Premiership|1953]]\n*'''[[McClelland Trophy]]'''\n** '''(2)''': [[1997 AFL season|1997]], [[2009 AFL season|2009]]\n\n===Individual===\n{{main|List of St Kilda Football Club individual honours}}\n{{col-float |firstcol=18em}}\n\n====Trevor Barker Award====\n{{main|Trevor Barker Award}}\n\n====Brownlow Medal====\n{{see also|Brownlow Medal}}\n* [[Robert Harvey (footballer)|Robert Harvey]], 1997 and 1998\n* [[Tony Lockett]], 1987\n* [[Ross G. Smith|Ross Smith]], 1967\n* [[Ian Stewart (Australian rules footballer)|Ian Stewart]], 1965 and 1966\n* [[Verdun Howell]], 1959\n* [[Neil Roberts (Australian footballer)|Neil Roberts]], 1958\n* [[Brian Gleeson (Australian rules footballer)|Brian Gleeson]], 1957\n* [[Colin Watson (footballer)|Colin Watson]], 1925\n\n====Michael Tuck Medal====\n{{see also|Michael Tuck Medal}}\n* [[Jason Gram]]: 2008\n* [[Robert Harvey (footballer)|Robert Harvey]]: 2004\n* [[Nicky Winmar]]: 1996\n{{col-float-break |nextcol=18em}}\n\n====Leigh Matthews Trophy====\n{{see also|Leigh Matthews Trophy}}\n* [[Nick Riewoldt]], 2004\n* [[Robert Harvey (footballer)|Robert Harvey]], 1997\n* [[Tony Lockett]], 1987\n\n====Coleman Medal====\n{{see also|Coleman Medal}}\n* [[Fraser Gehrig]], 2004 and 2005\n* [[Tony Lockett]], 1987 and 1991\n* [[Bill Young (Australian rules footballer)|Bill Young]], 1956\n* [[Bill Mohr]], 1936\n* [[Charlie Baker (footballer)|Charlie Baker]], 1902\n\n====AFL Rising Star award====\n{{see also|AFL Rising Star award}}\n* [[Nick Riewoldt]], 2002\n* [[Justin Koschitzke]], 2001\n\n====Norm Smith Medal====\n{{see also|Norm Smith Medal}}\n* [[Lenny Hayes]], 2010 Grand Final\n{{col-float-break |nextcol=24em}}\n\n====Australian Football Hall of Fame====\n{{see also|Australian Football Hall of Fame}}\n* [[Darrel Baldock]], legend\n* [[Roy Cazaly]], legend\n* [[Alex Jesaulenko]], legend\n* [[Tony Lockett]], legend\n* [[Ian Stewart (Australian rules footballer)|Ian Stewart]], legend\n* [[Vic Cumberland]]\n* [[Carl Ditterich]]\n* [[Wels Eicke]]\n* [[Les Foote]]\n* [[Robert Harvey (footballer)|Robert Harvey]]\n* [[Allan Jeans]] (inducted as coach)\n* [[Dave McNamara]]\n* [[Bill Mohr]]\n* [[Neil Roberts (Australian footballer)|Neil Roberts]]\n* [[Ross G. Smith|Ross Smith]]\n* [[Colin Watson (footballer)|Colin Watson]]\n* [[Verdun Howell]]\n{{col-float-end}}\n\n====St Kilda Football Club's Hall of Fame====\nSt Kilda Football Club's Hall of Fame was established in 2003. Club identities, past or present, are selected and inducted into the club's hall of fame by a St Kilda Football Club Hall of Fame committee.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://saints.com.au/Saints/TheClub/History/HallofFame/tabid/5391/Default.aspx |title=Hall of Fame \u2013 Official AFL Website of the St Kilda Football Club |publisher=Saints.com.au |date= |accessdate=10 December 2011}}</ref> At each gala event, at least one inductee is selected to be elevated to club legend status.\n\nSt Kilda's most recent hall of fame induction was held at the Palladium at Crown Casino in Melbourne on 24 July 2010 with three new inductees added.<ref>{{cite web|last=Gigliotti|first=Vanessa|title=Lockett Honoured as a Saints Legend|url=http://www.saints.com.au/season2010/news/newsarticle/tabid/5315/newsid/98917/default.aspx|date=24 July 2010|publisher=Official St Kilda Website}}</ref> The St Kilda Football Club Hall of Fame committee for 2010 featured Ross Smith, Greg Westaway, John Beveridge, Russell Holmesby, Neil Roberts, Allan Jeans and Danny Frawley. Previous inductions were held in 2003, 2007 and 2008, with 13 identities inducted in 2003, 12 in 2007 and 12 in 2008.\n{{col-float |firstcol=18em}}\n'''2003 Inductees'''\n* [[Darrel Baldock]]  ~  Legend\n* [[Ian Stewart (Australian rules footballer)|Ian Stewart]]\n* [[Tony Lockett]]\n* [[Trevor Barker]]\n* [[Carl Ditterich]]\n* [[Verdun Howell]]\n* [[Nicky Winmar]]\n* [[Ross G. Smith|Ross Smith]]\n* [[Neil Roberts (Australian footballer)|Neil Roberts]]\n* [[Bill Mohr]]\n* [[Dave McNamara]]\n* [[Allan Jeans]]\n* [[Ian Drake]]\n{{col-float-break |nextcol=18em}}\n'''2007 Inductees'''\n* [[Ian Stewart (Australian rules footballer)|Ian Stewart]]  ~  Legend\n* [[Harold Bray]]\n* [[Barry Breen]]\n* [[Jack Davis (footballer)|Jack Davis]]\n* [[Keith Drinan]]\n* [[Wels Eicke]]\n* [[Danny Frawley]]\n* [[Graham Huggins]]\n* [[Stewart Loewe]]\n* [[Alan Morrow]]\n* [[Bob Murray (Australian footballer)|Bob Murray]]\n* [[Kevin Neale]]\n* [[Travis Payze]]\n{{col-float-break |nextcol=18em}}\n'''2008 Inductees'''\n* [[Allan Jeans]]  ~  Legend\n* [[Nathan Burke]]\n* [[Greg Burns (Australian rules footballer)|Greg Burns]]\n* [[Gary Colling]]\n* [[Bill Cubbins]]\n* [[Brian Gleeson (Australian rules footballer)|Brian Gleeson]]\n* [[Daryl Griffiths]]\n* [[Barry Lawrence]]\n* [[Brian Mynott]]\n* [[Des Nisbet]]\n* [[Lance Oswald]]\n* [[Bruce Phillips]]\n* [[Colin Watson (footballer)|Colin Watson]]\n{{col-float-break |nextcol=18em}}\n'''2010 Inductees'''\n* [[Tony Lockett]]  ~  Legend\n* [[Jeff Sarau]]\n* [[Ian Synman]]\n* [[Ken Walker]]\n{{col-float-end}}\n\n==Records and statistics==\n{{Further|List of St Kilda Football Club records and statistics}}\n\n* '''Biggest winning margin:''' 139 points (2005, Round 22, v Brisbane Lions)\n* '''Largest attendance at a home game:''' 72,669 (1978, Waverley Park, v Collingwood)\n* '''Most premiership points in a season:''' 80 (2009)\n* '''Most consecutive wins:''' 19 (2009, Rounds 1\u201319)\n\n==Membership and attendance==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;\"\n! Year \n! Members Tally\n! Average Home Attendance\n|-\n||\t1984\t||\t<center> 4,930</center>      ||      <center> 17,185</center>\n|-\n||\t1985\t||\t<center> 5,708</center>      ||      <center> 15,489</center>\n|-\n||\t1986\t||\t<center> 4,321</center>      ||      <center> 15,214</center>\n|-\n||\t1987\t||\t<center> 3,924</center>      ||      <center> 18,069</center>\n|-\n||\t1988\t||\t<center> 5,799</center>      ||      <center> 19,499</center>\n|-\n||\t1989\t||\t<center> 8,360</center>      ||      <center> 20,483</center>\n|-\n||\t1990\t||\t<center>11,361</center>      ||      <center> 31,520</center>\n|-\n||\t1991\t||\t<center> 9,765</center>      ||      <center> 27,757</center>\n|-\n||\t1992\t||\t<ce